    "forr": "Government argues the pause lets it redirect money to frontline services, health-worker recruitment and hospital facilities rather than a costly governance transition, and cites unresolved issues such as pension impacts for health-care workers. Provides legal clarity for halting the transition. The minister said the civil-immunity clause was added partly in response to concerns raised by the interim board chair.",
